parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure (Fuel Pump and Fuel Injection Seal)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the fuel pump fails to pump sufficient gas to the engine
the fuel injection seal hardens due to high temperatures

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking of the accelerator pedal can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks to the floor
the pedal feels soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and even fatalities. The inability to stop the vehicle using the brakes can result in severe consequences.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unintentionally
often when shifting gears or applying the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the low/high beam switch can cause the headlamp high beams to stay on continuously, which can lead to glare and discomfort for oncoming traffic, potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The headlamp high beams stay on continuously
the low/high beam switch does not function properly
the high beams do not switch to low beams when intended.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine wiring harness can cause the engine to lock up, leading to engine damage, and potentially resulting in a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle experiences a complete loss of power

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the differential can cause loss of power to the wheels, leading to reduced traction, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Grinding or whining noise from the differential
loss of power to the wheels

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transaxle seal can cause fluid leaks, leading to premature wear on the transaxle and potentially causing loss of power to the wheels, reduced traction, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: grinding or whining noise from the transaxle
loss of power to the wheels.
